Phase 7 — Onboarding + Accessibility Audit:
	Branch: phase/7-onboarding-accessibility
	- Add Quit WireBar button to the popover or Settings menu
	- Check Location Services authorization on launch and prompt user if not granted (SSID requires it)
	- Add menu bar option to show Wi-Fi signal strength (e.g. dBm or signal bars) next to the icon
	- Implement first-run detection (check for first launch flag in UserDefaults)
	- Implement OnboardingView — welcome screen introducing WireBar
	- Implement setup wizard step: Location Services explanation and permission request
	- (Removed — privileged helper no longer needed with Network Extension framework)
	- Implement setup wizard step: auto-detect installed VPNs, present for user confirmation
	- Implement setup wizard step: configure menu bar display preferences
	- Implement setup wizard completion — app is ready
	- Full accessibility audit — VoiceOver labels on every element (catch gaps from Phases 1-6)
	- Accessibility audit — keyboard navigation via Tab through all interactive elements
	- Accessibility audit — VoiceOver value announcements for all toggles
	- Accessibility audit — respect reduced motion system setting
	- Accessibility audit — respect high contrast / increased contrast system settings
	- Edge case polish: Wi-Fi off state
	- Edge case polish: missing VPN CLI (grayed out with warning icon and tooltip)
	- Edge case polish: external IP fetch failure ("Unavailable" with retry)
	- Edge case polish: no VPN profiles found (helpful message)
	- Edge case polish: no networks available
	- Edge case polish: very long network names (truncation)
	- Edge case polish: empty VPN list
	- Full Settings window review — all tabs consistent, all options functional
	- Update .taskpaper with any discoveries or adjustments
	- Manual test against PRD user stories 55-58 (first-run experience)
	- Manual test against PRD user stories 65-67 (accessibility)
	- Manual test against PRD user stories 49, 53-54 (settings, crash reporting opt-in)
	- Manual test: delete preferences and launch as new user — full onboarding flow
	- Regression test: ALL prior user stories (full regression)

Phase 8 — Release Prep:
	Branch: phase/8-release-prep
	Pre-Release Documentation:
		- Update SPEC.md, PRD.md, DESIGN_DECISIONS.md to reflect all changes from development
		- Write user documentation with screenshots and annotated images
		- Write developer documentation with architecture diagrams and module relationship maps
		- Create README.md for GitHub (landing page until website exists)
		- Finalize privacy policy
		- Finalize EULA
		- Create BSL LICENSE file with 3-year conversion date
	Release Infrastructure:
		- Write release script: xcodebuild → codesign → notarize → staple → create .dmg
		- Set up Sparkle appcast generation (generate_appcast from .dmg releases)
		- Configure GitHub Releases for hosting .dmg and appcast XML
		- Test full release pipeline end-to-end (build, sign, notarize, staple, .dmg, appcast)
	LemonSqueezy Setup:
		- Create product listing on LemonSqueezy ($12.99, description, screenshots) (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Configure license key settings in LemonSqueezy dashboard (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Test purchase flow end-to-end with test mode (Scott) @tags(scott)
	Pre-Release Cleanup:
		- Clean up git history (squash/rebase early commits) before making release-ready
		- Remove any TODO/FIXME comments or resolve them
		- Final code review pass
		- Verify all user-facing strings use String(localized:)
		- Verify no secrets or credentials in repo
	Name & Branding:
		- Final name decision (if "WireBar" had conflicts, apply chosen name everywhere)
		- Register domain name (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Update bundle display name, app icon, and all branding assets
	Competitive Research:
		- Competitive research pass 2 — refine marketing angle and positioning @tags(research)
	Beta Testing:
		- Recruit 3-5 beta testers from friends (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Request at least one tester on older macOS (Sequoia or earlier) @tags(scott)
		- Distribute .dmg directly to beta testers (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Collect feedback (group chat or simple form) (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- 2-week beta window
		- Exit criteria: no crashes and no broken user stories for 3 consecutive days
		- Fix all critical issues found during beta
		- Collect DiagnosticReports from beta testers for crash visibility
	Launch:
		- Build final release .dmg
		- Run full release pipeline (sign, notarize, staple)
		- Create GitHub Release with .dmg and appcast
		- Publish product on LemonSqueezy (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Update README / landing page with download link
		- Scott's go/no-go decision (Scott) @tags(scott)

Post-Launch — V1.x Roadmap:
	V1.1 — Crash Reporting:
		- Create Sentry account and project (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Integrate Sentry SDK via SPM
		- Implement opt-in crash reporting toggle in Settings (off by default)
		- Implement per-crash consent dialog for non-opted-in users ("WireBar quit unexpectedly. Send a crash report?")
		- Sentry SDK only initializes after user opts in — never before
		- Keep Sentry DSN out of public repo (environment variable or build setting)
	V1.x — Custom VPN Support:
		- Implement non-elevated custom VPN support (user provides name + CLI commands)
		- Custom VPN commands run at user-level permissions only (no privileged helper)
		- Settings UI for adding/editing/removing custom VPNs
	V1.x — VPN Library Expansion:
		- Add pre-configured CLI commands for popular VPNs: Mullvad, NordVPN, ExpressVPN, ProtonVPN, Surfshark, CyberGhost, OpenVPN, Cisco AnyConnect, GlobalProtect
	Future Improvements:
		- Move release pipeline to GitHub Actions CI
		- Landing page / marketing website (when domain is secured)
		- Consider user feedback platforms (Canny-style voting) if user base grows
		- Consider subreddit or community if user base grows
		- Setapp integration
		- App Store version (reduced feature set)

